        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 21 at 4:46PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 445 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Knickerbocker, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Christoval.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
